    "24": { correct: "d", correctText: "Satavahanas", exp: "The Satavahana rulers used matronymics — names derived from the mother (e.g. Gautamiputra Satakarni, Vasishthiputra Pulumavi). The other listed groups did not characteristically do so." },
    "25": { correct: "d", correctText: "Stridhana was not inherited by the children without the permission of the husband", exp: "This statement is incorrect — stridhana was inherited by a woman’s children (especially daughters) and did not require the husband’s permission. The paternal estate divided equally among sons and the definition of stridhana as marriage gifts are correctly stated." },
    "26": { correct: "b", correctText: "Vajji", exp: "The Vajji (Vrijji) confederacy was a gana/sangha (oligarchic republic). Magadha, Avanti and Kosala were monarchies, not oligarchies." },
